small>\n* [[The Soul of John Black|John Bigham]] \u2013 guitar <small>(tracks 5, 10)</small>\n* [[Jeff Bass]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 1)</small>\n* [[The 45 King]] \u2013 production <small>(track 3)</small>\n* [[Dido (singer)|Dido]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 3)</small>\n* [[Paul Rosenberg (music manager)|Paul \"Bunyan\" Rosenberg]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 4)</small>\n* Steve Berman \u2013 vocals <small>(track 6)</small>\n* Thomas Rounds \u2013 engineering assistance <small>(track 7)</small>\n* [[RBX]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 9)</small>\n* [[Sticky Fingaz]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 9)</small>\n* Camara Kambon \u2013 keyboards <small>(track 9)</small>\n* Dina Rae \u2013 vocals <small>(track 13)</small>\n* [[Bizarre (rapper)|Bizarre]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 14)</small>\n* [[Snoop Dogg]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 15)</small>\n* [[Xzibit]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 15)</small>\n* [[Nate Dogg]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 15)</small>\n* [[D12|D-12]] \u2013 vocals <small>(track 17)</small>\n* Mike Butler \u2013 engineering <small>(track 17)</small>\n* Aaron Lepley \u2013 engineering <small>(track 17)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n; Credits\n{{div col}}\n* Dr. Dre \u2013 executive production\n* Dean Geistlinger \u2013 Interscope A&R direction\n* DJ Mormile \u2013 Interscope A&R direction\n* [[Paul Rosenberg (music manager)|Paul D. Rosenberg, Esq.]] \u2013 Eminem management\n* Cutler & Sedlmayr, LLP \u2013 Eminem legal\n* Joel Martin \u2013 F.B.T. productions management\n* Howard Hertz, Esq. \u2013 F.B.T. productions legal\n* Chris Clancy \u2013 Interscope product management\n* Les Scurry \u2013 Interscope production coordination\n* Joe Mama-Nitzberg \u2013 photography & art coordination\n* Jason Noto \u2013 art direction & design\n* Jonathan \"Xtra Gangsta\" Mannion \u2013 photography\n* Kirdis Tucker \u2013 Aftermath project coordination\n* Larry Chatman \u2013 Aftermath project coordination\n* Peter Paterno, Esq. \u2013 Aftermath legal\n* Wendy Ellen Bass \u2013 WEB A&R direction\n* Karen Pinegar \u2013 F.B.T. assistance\n* Sarah Catlett \u2013 F.B.T. assistance\n* Richard Segal Huredia \u2013 engineering\n* Steve King \u2013 engineering\n* Chris Conway \u2013 engineering\n* Mike Butler \u2013 engineering\n* Lance Pierre \u2013 engineering\n* Rob Ebeling \u2013 engineering\n* James McCrone \u2013 engineering\n* Aaron Lepley \u2013 engineering\n* Rich Behrens \u2013 engineering\n* Michelle Forbes \u2013 engineering\n* Akane Nakamura \u2013 engineering\n* Brian \"Big Bass\" Gardner \u2013 mastering\n* Cara Lewis \u2013 Eminem booking\n* Marc Labelle \u2013 Eminem road management\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"  style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2000\u201301)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{albumchart|Australia|1|artist=Eminem|album=The Marshall Mathers LP|accessdate=May 28, 2010|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Austria|1|artist=Eminem|album=The Marshall Mathers LP|accessdate=May 28, 2010|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Flanders|1|artist=Eminem|album=The Marshall Mathers LP|accessdate=May 28, 2010|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Wallonia|3|artist=Eminem|album=The Marshall Mathers LP|accessdate=May 28, 2010|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Canadian Albums ([[Canadian Albums Chart|CRIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.7294&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=c6btf3r8hs459qqt5ln3o3dcv5|title=Top Albums/CDs \u2013 Volume 71, No. 5, June 05 2000|work=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]|accessdate=May 28, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020011734/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.7294&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=c6btf3r8hs459qqt5ln3o3dcv5|archive-date=October 20, 2012|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{albumchart|BillboardCanada|1|artist=Eminem|album=The Ma